  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally refers to the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Legal definitions typically include:\n\n1. Basic elements:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming \"dirty\" money into seemingly \"clean\" money\n- Disguising the origins of criminal proceeds\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing the funds originated from criminal activity\n- Attempting to hide the source of funds\n- Promoting unlawful activity\n\n3. Typical stages:\n- Placement: Introducing illegal funds into financial system\n- Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions\n- Integration: Reintroducing funds as apparently legitimate income\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions involve:\n- Criminal intent\n- Financial transactions\n- Proceeds from specified unlawful activities\n\n5. Key legislation:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- International: Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n\nThis overview provides general legal concepts, but specific definitions vary by jurisdiction and context.",
